se.hig.exte.restcontroller

Class SettingsController

  • java.lang.Object
    • se.hig.exte.restcontroller.SettingsController

  • @RestController
 @RequestMapping(value="/settings")
public class SettingsController
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is a RestController class responsible for mapping HTTP requests for the /settings path. It contains mappings of end-points to services that operate on Settings records in the database.

      • saveSettings

        @PostMapping(value="/")
public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<Settings> saveSettings(@Valid @RequestBody
                                                                                               @Valid Settings settings,
                                                                                               javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest request)
        Saves a Settings object to the database. Returns a "FORBIDDEN" HTTP status code if the Settings object already exists. Updates are not allowed.
        Parameters:
        settings - The Settings object to save.
        request - The incoming HTTP request.
        Returns:
        A ResponseEntity containing the saved Settings object, in JSON format accompanied by an HTTP status code. Returns:
        • 200 if the request is successful.
        • 401 if the user is not logged in
        • 403 if the tries to save a Settings object that has an ID value. ID should be null.
